==English==
===Phrase===
'''(the) cat among the pigeons'''
#To cause alarm. 
#*The Times 19 September 1994: 
::Professor Steven Hawkin '''put the cat among the pigeons''' last week with his cheery remarks about commet Machholz-2 which some astronomers believe could be heading our way."
#*If you '''set the cat among the pigeons''', you will cause a [[flutter in the dovecote]].
====Usage Note====
Preceeded by "put" or "set".
====Reference====
1996: Brewer's Dictionary of Phrase and Fable (Cassell).